  "text": "Oct-4 may be regulated by the Wnt pathway and has the ability to reprogram committed somatic cells, inducing their dedifferentiation by reverting them to a more developmentally potent state [CITATION_1] . Keratinocytes that overexpress Oct-4 can differentiate into other cell types, based on expression of genes characteristic of neuronal cells: nestin, neuN, and Sox-1. This indicates that Oct-4 may be a master regulator of the pluripotent state in mammalian cells.",
